08/05/2011
ATHENS, Greece -- Police clashed with protesting doctors outside the health ministry building in downtown Athens on Friday (May 6th). 
The demonstration was held as part of a three-hour work stoppage in public hospitals in greater Athens. 
Police used pepper spray to disperse protestors. 
Trade unions in the country are preparing for a general strike on Wednesday. 
(Ethnos, Eleftherotypia, SKAI, Mega TV - 06/05/11)
